eyefeatures.utils._get_angle(dx, dy, degrees=True)¶

Method calculates an angle of movement from (0, 0) to (dx, dy). Formally, method returns a non-negative angle in anticlockwise direction in cartesian system between x-axis and vector (dx, dy).

Return type:

float

eyefeatures.utils._get_angle2(x1, y1, x2, y2, degrees=True, smallest=False)¶

Method calculates a non-negative angle in anticlockwise direction based on 2 points (i.e. between two vectors) (x1, y1) and (x2, y2) in cartesian system.

eyefeatures.utils._get_angle3(x0, y0, x1, y1, x2, y2, degrees=True, smallest=False)¶

Get angle at (x0, y0) based on 2 other points defining vectors (x1 - x0, y1 - y0) and (x2 - x0, y2 - y0).
